<section id="adding-task-ids-to-items-in-editors" version="5.0" xmlns="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook"
                                                                xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude"
                                                                xmlns:xl="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" >
  <title>Adding Task IDs to items in editors</title>
  <anchor role="helpid" id="guidancerSpecTestCaseEditorContextId">Test Case Editor</anchor>
  <anchor role="helpid" id="testSuiteEditorContextId">Test Suite Editor</anchor>
  <anchor role="helpid" id="guidancerTestJobEditorContextId">Test Job Editor</anchor>
  <para>
    You can add a Task ID to a Test Case, Test Suite or Test Job in
    the relevant editor. You can add a task ID to the item itself,
    but not to other items used in it (unless you edit them in their
    own editor).
  </para>
  <orderedlist>
    <listitem>
      <para>
        Open the editor for the item you want to add a task ID to.
      </para>
    </listitem>
    <listitem>
      <para>
        Enter a task ID in the <emphasis>Task ID</emphasis> field in
        the Properties View.
      </para>
    </listitem>
    <listitem>
      <para>
        Save the changes
      </para>
    </listitem>
    <listitem>
      <para>
        Task IDs cannot be overwritten when an item is reused.
      </para>
    </listitem>
  </orderedlist>
</section>